Want something sweet?

65
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,530
I've got
some peppermint sticks.

66
00:02:54,530 --> 00:02:56,700
I made them myself.

67
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:58,410
Mnh-Mnh.

68
00:02:58,450 --> 00:03:00,710
They'll make you smile.

69
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:02,370
No.

70
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:04,420
I don't know why we had to
sit through a lecture

71
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:05,290
about getting a cutie mark.

72
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:08,090
I mean, waiting
for your cutie mark

73
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:09,210
is so last week.

74
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:10,550
You've got yours.

75
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:11,840
I just got mine.

76
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,510
We all have them already.

77
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:14,640
[ Gasps ]

78
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:18,100
I mean, almost all of us
have them already.

79
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,310
Don't worry, you two,

80
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:22,520
You're still totally invited
to my cute-ceañera this weekend.

81
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:24,600
It's going to be
amazing.

82
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:28,570
It's a party celebrating me
and my fantastic cutie mark.

83
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:30,650
How can it not be?

84
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:32,240
Bump, bump,

85
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,530
sugar lump, rump!

86
00:03:33,570 --> 00:03:34,820
[ Both laugh ]

87
00:03:34,870 --> 00:03:36,370
Give me a break.

88
00:03:36,370 --> 00:03:38,410
See you
this weekend...

89
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:40,370
[ both laugh ]

90
00:03:40,410 --> 00:03:42,210
Both:
...blank flanks!

91
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:44,120
[ Both laugh ]

92
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:48,210
It's not fair!

93
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:49,840
It's just not fair!

94
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:52,220
Don't get your mane
in a tangle.

95
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:53,760
You'll get your cutie mark.

96
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,890
Everypony gets one
eventually.

97
00:03:55,890 --> 00:03:58,640
But I don't want one
eventually.

98
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,390
I want one right now!

99
00:04:00,390 --> 00:04:03,390
I can't go to Diamond Tiara's
cute-ceañera without one.

100
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,810
I just can't!

101
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:06,060
'Course you can.

102
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:09,900
You know, I was the last pony
in my class to get a cutie mark,

103
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:12,190
and I couldn't be prouder
of it.

104
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:14,570
I knew my future
was to run Sweet Apple Acres,

105
00:04:14,570 --> 00:04:17,200
and these bright, shiny apples
sealed the deal.

106
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,240
[ Gasps ]

107
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,240
Come to think of it,

108
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:21,750
Granny Smith was the last one
in her class, too.

109
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:23,790
Huh.
Same with Big Mcintosh.

110
00:04:23,830 --> 00:04:27,210
I really don't see how that's
supposed to make me feel better.

111
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:29,920
It probably means that being
the last one in your class

112
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,260
to get a cutie mark
runs in the family.

113
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:33,880
"Runs in the family"?

114
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:37,640
"Runs in the family"!

115
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,680
You've got apples
for your cutie mark.

116
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,520
Granny Smith
has an apple pie.

117
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:43,730
Big Mcintosh
has an apple half.

118
00:04:43,810 --> 00:04:46,940
My unique talent must have
something to do with apples!

119
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:49,360
Apples, apples, apples!

120
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,650
[ Crash! ]

121
00:04:50,690 --> 00:04:52,940
[ Sighs ]

122
00:04:52,990 --> 00:04:54,900
Apples.

123
00:04:56,990 --> 00:05:00,620
Get your delicious,
nutritious apples here.

124
00:05:00,660 --> 00:05:04,540
Delicious and nutritious
and so many uses.

125
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:05,660
[ Chomp! ]

126
00:05:05,710 --> 00:05:08,540
You can eat 'em,
play with 'em...

127
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:12,710
[ Crash! ]
Pony:
Hey! Watch it!

128
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:16,300
...create fine art
for your home with 'em.

129
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,890
You'd have to be crazy not to
get a bushel of your very own.

130
00:05:21,850 --> 00:05:23,850
[ Chuckles ]
She's so creative.

131
00:05:23,890 --> 00:05:24,850
You, sir!

132
00:05:24,890 --> 00:05:26,600
Care to buy
some apples?

133
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,600
Uh, no, thanks.

134
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,730
Why not?

135
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:31,060
I have plenty at home.

136
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:32,150
Are you sure?

137
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:34,360
Yes, I'm pretty sure.
You're pretty sure,

138
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,530
But you're not absolutely,
positively,

139
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:38,610
completely, superduper sure,
are you?

140
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:41,830
Uh, if I buy some apples,
will you please leave me alone?

141
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:43,040
All right!

142
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:48,330
You forgot your change!

143
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:49,920
Apple Bloom:
Whoo-Hoo!

144
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:53,590
There's how you sell some apples
and get a cutie mark.

145
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:55,840
So, what does my cutie mark
look like --

146
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,630
A shopping bag
full of apples?

147
00:05:57,670 --> 00:05:59,760
A satisfied customer
eating an apple?

148
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,800
Hmm.

149
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:04,720
Maybe I got to increase
my sales figures first.

150
00:06:04,770 --> 00:06:06,890
You touch it,
you buy it!

151
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:08,770
We take cash or credit.

152
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:10,560
I'm sorry, ma'am.

153
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,770
Ma'am!

154
00:06:11,810 --> 00:06:13,610
[ Sighs ]

155
00:06:13,610 --> 00:06:15,730
Now, Apple Bloom,
you can't just...

156
00:06:15,780 --> 00:06:18,030
That'll be four bits.

157
00:06:18,070 --> 00:06:19,950
I didn't put those
in my bag.

158
00:06:19,990 --> 00:06:21,370
Likely story.

159
00:06:21,410 --> 00:06:22,660
Four bits, lady.

160
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:23,530
Apple Bloom!

161
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:25,990
I am really, really sorry
about that.

162
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,120
She's new.

163
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:30,080
Here. Take these.
No charge.

164
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,000
And these.

165
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,840
And these.

166
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,550
[ Grunts ]

167
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,840
Y'all come back now,
you hear?

168
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,140
What?

169
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:48,600
Sorry, little sis, but your
apple-selling days are over.

170
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:49,520
What?!

171
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,690
But how else am I gonna get
my cutie mark?

172
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:54,110
Home. Now!

173
00:06:54,150 --> 00:06:55,610
Pbht!

174
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:57,070
Hmph.

175
00:06:57,110 --> 00:06:58,070
[ Sighs ]

176
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,190
Listen, sugar cube,

177
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:01,860
I know it's hard to wait
for your very own cutie mark,

178
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,030
but you just can't
force it.

179
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:06,910
Besides, you're not
that grown up just yet.

180
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:10,210
Ain't there other fillies
in your class without one?

181
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:12,710
Well, twist
doesn't have hers yet.

182
00:07:12,710 --> 00:07:13,960
Do you think
you'd feel better

183
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,540
if you went to the party
with her?

184
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:17,920
Mm-Hmm.
Well, there you go.

185
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,800
Bet you and Twist would have
a great time together.

186
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,880
Now, run along
and find your friend.

187
00:07:22,930 --> 00:07:25,050
You're sure you don't want me
to stick around

188
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,560
Till the end of the market?

189
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:29,520
Hey, who's been using
my racket?!

190
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,690
Yeah, I'm sure.

191
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:39,940
Oh, what's up,
Apple Bloom?

192
00:07:39,990 --> 00:07:41,190
So, I was thinking.

193
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:44,660
Maybe we could go to Diamond
Tiara's cute-ceañera together.

194
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:46,580
I-I don't have
a cutie mark.

195
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:48,200
You don't have
a cutie mark.

196
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,160
Well, um...

197
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,660
[ Lock unlatches ]

198
00:07:52,750 --> 00:07:53,870
[ Gasps ]

199
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,130
Isn't my cutie mark
swell?

200
00:07:56,170 --> 00:07:58,750
I've always loved
making my own savory sweets,

201
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,880
but it took me some time
to discover

202
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:02,920
that it was
my super-special talent.

203
00:08:02,970 --> 00:08:05,220
Pretty sweet, huh?

204
00:08:05,260 --> 00:08:06,930
Yeah.

205
00:08:06,930 --> 00:08:09,140
Pretty...sweet.

206
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:10,390
Hey...

207
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:14,270
this doesn't mean we can't go
to the cute-ceañera together.

208
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:17,230
You're still gonna come
to the party, aren't you?

209
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,940
Of course she will.

210
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:22,190
It's not like being the only
pony there without a cutie mark

211
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:26,110
will be, like, the most
embarrassing thing ever.

212
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:27,120
[ Both laugh ]

213
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:34,790
Whoa.

214
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:37,960
Looks like somepony's got a dark
cloud hanging over her head.

215
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:40,800
Let me do something
about that.

216
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,380
What's the matter,
kid?

217
00:08:45,430 --> 00:08:46,470
[ Inhales deeply ]

218
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:48,310
[ Rapidly ] There's
a cute-ceañera this afternoon,

219
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:49,680
