But I want it now!

226
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:03,650
Cutie mark?

227
00:09:03,690 --> 00:09:05,990
I can get you a cutie mark
like that.

228
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:08,660
Applejack says these things
take time.

229
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:10,830
I have to just wait for it
to happen.

230
00:09:10,830 --> 00:09:14,500
Why wait for something to happen
when you can make it happen?

231
00:09:14,540 --> 00:09:16,420
But Applejack
says that --

232
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:18,500
Hey, who are you
gonna listen to --

233
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:21,420
Applejack or the pony
who was first in her class

234
00:09:21,420 --> 00:09:22,590
to get a cutie mark?

235
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,130
I always liked flying
and all,

236
00:09:24,170 --> 00:09:26,010
but I was going nowhere
in a hurry.

237
00:09:26,010 --> 00:09:27,840
It wasn't until
my very first race

238
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,010
that I discovered
a serious need for speed,

239
00:09:30,050 --> 00:09:33,060
and -- Kazaam! --
This sweet baby appeared

240
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,730
as fast as lightning.

241
00:09:36,850 --> 00:09:38,940
[ Grunting ]

242
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,770
That's right.

243
00:09:40,810 --> 00:09:42,190
Stretch out those legs.

244
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:44,030
Got to be
nice and loose.

245
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:46,650
The key here is to try
as many things as possible

246
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:47,700
as quickly as possible.

247
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:50,490
One of them is bound to lead
to your cutie mark.

248
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:51,620
Are you ready?

249
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:52,740
I'm ready!

250
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:55,160
I said,
are you ready?!

251
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,910
I'm ready!

