[ Whistle blows ]

265
00:10:51,970 --> 00:10:53,220
[ Growling ]

266
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:56,470
Wha! Whoa!

267
00:10:56,930 --> 00:10:59,020
[ Screech! ]

268
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,190
[ Crash! ]

269
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:04,110
[ Wheels squeaking ]

270
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:05,940
Tried that one.

271
00:11:05,980 --> 00:11:07,820
Tried that one.
Tried that one.

272
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:08,900
[ Both giggling ]

273
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:11,820
Your new outfit is, like,
perfect for the party.

274
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,950
Diamond Tiara:
I know.
[ Gasps ]

275
00:11:12,990 --> 00:11:15,120
It totally shows off
my new cutie mark.

276
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:16,790
I love being special.

277
00:11:16,830 --> 00:11:19,540
Can you imagine how embarrassing
it must be to be...

278
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,540
not special?

279
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:23,920
I don't even want to, like,
think about it.

280
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,960
Tried that one.

281
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,210
[ Groans ]
tried that one.

282
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:29,210
I'm doomed -- Doomed!

283
00:11:29,260 --> 00:11:32,550
I'll never find something
I'm good at!

284
00:11:32,590 --> 00:11:34,850
You look like you'd be good
at eating cupcakes.

285
00:11:34,890 --> 00:11:36,810
Eating cupcakes?

286
00:11:36,850 --> 00:11:38,720
Eating cupcakes?

287
00:11:38,770 --> 00:11:40,980
Eating cupcakes!

288
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:43,810
I really appreciate
all your help, Rainbow Dash.

289
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:45,270
You're a really great coach,

290
00:11:45,310 --> 00:11:47,730
and I've really
learned a lot from you,

291
00:11:47,770 --> 00:11:49,900
and I'm sure
I can learn a lot more,

292
00:11:49,940 --> 00:11:52,030
but I've got
some cupcakes to eat!

293
00:11:52,070 --> 00:11:53,860
See you
at the cute-ceañera!

294
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:57,240
Hold on, Pinkie Pie,
I'm coming!

295
00:11:57,280 --> 00:12:00,330
I can't believe
I didn't think of this --

296
00:12:00,330 --> 00:12:02,660
A cupcake-eating
cutie mark.

297
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:03,920
It's so obvious.

298
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:06,170
Now,
where are those cupcakes?

299
00:12:06,210 --> 00:12:08,210
I'm ready to chow down!

300
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,960
I don't have
any cupcakes.

301
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:11,760
Oh.
[ Gasps ]

302
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,840
But you look like you'd be good
at helping me make some!

303
00:12:14,890 --> 00:12:19,140
I guess a making-cupcakes
cutie mark could work, too.

304
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:21,560
* All you have to do
Is take a cup of flour *

305
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,270
* Add it to the mix

306
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:25,520
* Now just take a little
Something sweet, not sour *

307
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:27,610
* A bit of salt,
Just a pinch *

308
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:29,230
* Baking these treats
Is such a cinch *

309
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:31,280
* Add a teaspoon of vanilla

310
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,070
* Add a little more,
And you count to four, *

311
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:35,110
* And you never get
Your fill-a *

312
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:37,030
* Cupcakes,
So sweet and tasty *

313
00:12:37,070 --> 00:12:38,910
* Cupcakes,
Don't be too hasty *

314
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:42,540
* Cupcakes,
Cupcakes, cupcakes, cupcakes! *

315
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:44,160
[ Mixer whirring ]

316
00:12:47,290 --> 00:12:48,790
[ Smoke hisses ]

317
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:51,800
[ Coughs ]

318
00:12:53,970 --> 00:12:56,050
[ Sizzling ]
Hot! Hot! Hot!

319
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:59,140
Ooh! Those look much better
than the last batch.

320
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:04,180
[ Munching ]

321
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:05,190
Yuck!

322
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:08,650
Guess I'm not cut out to be
a baker, either.

323
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:10,820
I just have to face it.

324
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:13,070
I'm gonna have
a blank flank forever!

325
00:13:13,110 --> 00:13:14,990
What about that?

326
00:13:14,990 --> 00:13:16,150
What about what?

327
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,320
Is there something
on my flank?

328
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:20,580
Is there? Is there?
Is there?

329
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:24,040
[ Gasps ]
A cutie mark!

330
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,120
It's a...

331
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,250
A measuring cup? No.

332
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:29,250
A mixing bowl? No.

333
00:13:29,290 --> 00:13:31,130
Are those cupcakes?

334
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:33,800
A tower of cupcakes, maybe.

335
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,260
[ Exhales sharply ]

336
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:37,380
Flour! It's flour!

337
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:38,680
Yay!
I guessed it!

338
00:13:38,680 --> 00:13:40,260
What game
do you want to play next?

339
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:42,100
Please say bingo.
Please say bingo.

340
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:45,140
Whoa! What's been
going on in here?

341
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:47,390
We've been making cupcakes.
Want to try one?

342
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,060
No, thank you,

343
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:53,400
not that they don't look
[sighs] delicious.

344
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:55,190
Twilight,
you have to help me.

345
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,280
What's the matter?

346
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,820
[ Inhales deeply ]

347
00:13:58,190 --> 00:14:00,460
Tiara's cute-ceañera is
today, and everypony in
my class will be there,

348
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,230
and they all have
their cutie marks,

349
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:02,110
and I want to get my cutie mark,

350
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:04,520
but I'm no good at selling
apples or hang-gliding
or making cupcakes,

351
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:06,420
but I want to go to the party,
but how can I go to the party

352
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:08,190
if I don't have my cutie mark,
which Pinkie Pie says

353
00:14:08,210 --> 00:14:10,520
I can't just make appear,
but I need it to appear

354
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:12,930
[Deliberately]
Right now!

355
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:15,670
Uh...I don't follow.

356
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:17,260
How can I help you?

357
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:20,180
You can use your magic
to make my cutie mark appear.

358
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:21,970
Oh, no, Apple Bloom.

359
00:14:22,010 --> 00:14:23,390
A cutie mark is something

360
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:25,890
that a pony has to discover
for herself.

361
00:14:25,930 --> 00:14:28,140
Please, Twilight,
just try.

362
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:29,100
I'm sorry, but --

363
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:31,360
Oh, please, please,
please, please, please!

364
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,480
All right, all right!

365
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,150
Oh, thank you,
thank you, thank you!

366
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:36,860
[ Tinkling ]

367
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:37,860
Yes!

368
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:40,280
I knew you could do...it.

369
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:43,280
I'm sorry, sweetie,
but I told you.

370
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:45,740
Try again!
Try again!

371
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:46,750
[ Sighs ]

372
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:48,290
[ Tinkling ]

373
00:14:58,510 --> 00:15:00,300
[ Gasps ]

374
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:02,390
Told you
that not even magic

375
00:15:02,430 --> 00:15:05,430
can make a cutie mark appear
before its time.

376
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:07,970
It's hopeless --
Hopeless!

377
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:10,020
I just won't go
to the party.

378
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:11,400
I can't go.

379
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:13,400
Everyone
will just laugh at me

380
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,860
and make fun of me
and call me names.

381
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:18,150
It will be the worst night
of my life.

382
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:20,780
I'm sure it won't be
as bad as all that.

383
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:21,570
Forget it.

384
00:15:21,610 --> 00:15:24,070
There's no way
I'm going to that...

385
00:15:26,450 --> 00:15:28,450
[ gulps ]
...party.

386
00:15:31,420 --> 00:15:33,290
[ Up-tempo music playing ]

387
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:43,010
How could I have forgotten
the time?

388
00:15:43,050 --> 00:15:44,260
How could I have forgotten

389
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:46,100
Pinkie Pie
was hosting the party?

390
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:48,770
How could I have forgotten
it was at Sugar Cube Corner?

391
00:15:48,770 --> 00:15:52,100
Don't forget your party hat,
forgetty forgeterson.

392
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:56,770
I have to get out of here
before anypony sees me.

393
00:16:01,950 --> 00:16:03,860
Diamond Tiara: Hey!

394
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:05,240
It's my cute-ceañera!

395
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:08,240
I'm supposed to get
the first bite of cake!

396
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:14,040
[ Popping loudly ]

397
00:16:28,180 --> 00:16:33,060
Okay, Apple Bloom,
almost there.

398
00:16:34,190 --> 00:16:35,730
[ Pitter! ]

399
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:39,860
[ Pitter! ]

400
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:42,150
[ Slurps ]

401
00:16:42,150 --> 00:16:44,150
[ Pitter! ]

402
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,160
Apple Bloom,
you made it!

403
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,290
After I heard about Twist,

404
00:16:51,290 --> 00:16:53,000
I was afraid
you wouldn't show up.

405
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,790
I sure am glad
you came to your senses

406
00:16:54,830 --> 00:16:56,290
about this whole
cutie-mark thing.

407
00:16:56,330 --> 00:16:59,170
These things happen when these
things are supposed to happen.

408
00:16:59,210 --> 00:17:01,840
Trying to rush it
will just drive you crazy.

409
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:02,800
I'll let you be.

410
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:04,880
Looks like your friends
want to talk to you.

411
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,180
[ Grunts ]

412
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:16,270
Well, well, well,
look who's here.

413
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:18,060
Nice outfit.

414
00:17:18,110 --> 00:17:21,270
Just something I, uh,
pulled together last minute.

415
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:23,400
I really shows off
your cutie mark.

416
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:25,280
Oh, wait. That's right.

417
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,450
You don't have one.

418
00:17:26,490 --> 00:17:28,240
I have a cutie mark.

419
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,990
What? Since when?

420
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:33,000
Since, um, earlier today.

421
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:35,290
Oh, really?
Let's see it.

422
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:39,290
I-I shouldn't.
I-I couldn't.

423
00:17:39,330 --> 00:17:42,170
My cutie mark
is so unbelievably amazing.

424
00:17:42,210 --> 00:17:44,460
I'm afraid
that if I show it off,

425
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:47,970
everyone will start paying
attention to me instead of you.

426
00:17:47,970 --> 00:17:50,970
Outshined at your own
cute-ceañera?

427
00:17:51,010 --> 00:17:54,140
Can you imagine
how embarrassing that would be?

428
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:55,390
Uh, forget it.

429
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:57,480
I didn't really
want to see it anyway.

430
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:59,650
Okay.
Well, I'm gonna go mingle.

431
00:17:59,650 --> 00:18:01,360
Enjoy your party.

432
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,230
[ Sighs ]

433
00:18:05,990 --> 00:18:07,320
[ Record scratches ]

434
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:09,070
[ All gasp ]

435
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:13,450
Oh, no!

436
00:18:13,490 --> 00:18:15,370
[ Laughs ]
Wow!

437
00:18:15,410 --> 00:18:18,000
That is an amazing
cutie mark.

438
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,250
[ Both laugh ]

439
00:18:19,290 --> 00:18:20,920
Nice try...

440
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,290
blank flank!
Blank flank!

441
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:23,630
[ Both laugh ]

442
00:18:23,670 --> 00:18:25,010
[ Scattered laughter ]

443
00:18:25,050 --> 00:18:26,050
Blank flank.

444
00:18:26,090 --> 00:18:29,130
Does one of you got a problem
with blank flanks?

445
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:30,140
[ All gasp ]

446
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:33,560
I said, you got a problem
with blank flanks?

447
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:37,390
The problem is, I mean, she's,
like, totally not special.

448
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:40,270
No, it means
she's full of potential.

449
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:42,310
It means she could be great
at anything.

450
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:46,360
The possibilities
are, like, endless.

451
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:48,570
She could be a great scientist

452
00:18:48,610 --> 00:18:50,320
or an amazing artist

453
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:51,990
or a famous writer.

454
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:55,160
She could even be mayor
of Ponyville someday.

455
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:58,040
And she's not stuck
being stuck-up like you two.

456
00:18:58,080 --> 00:18:59,710
[ Laughter ]

457
00:18:59,710 --> 00:19:01,670
Hey!
This is my party.

458
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:03,500
Why are two on her side?

459
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:05,630
Because...

460
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:06,550
[ gasps ]

461
00:19:06,550 --> 00:19:08,420
You don't have
any cutie marks, either?!

462
00:19:08,470 --> 00:19:10,630
I thought
I was the only one.

463
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:12,970
We thought
we were the only two.

464
00:19:13,010 --> 00:19:16,470
I, for one, think you are three
very lucky fillies.

465
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:19,560
Lucky?
How can they be lucky?

466
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:22,150
They still get to experience
the thrill

467
00:19:22,190 --> 00:19:25,320
of discovering who they are
and what they're meant to be.

468
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:28,570
And they've got all the time
in the world to figure it out,

469
00:19:28,570 --> 00:19:31,200
not just an afternoon.

470
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:32,530
[ Indistinct agreeing ]

471
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:33,990
Wow! Apple Bloom!

472
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:35,200
Do you really think
you can be anything?

473
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,030
I wish
I could be a scientist!

474
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:39,080
Maybe I got my cutie mark
too soon.

475
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:41,160
Hey,
what's everypony doing?

476
00:19:41,210 --> 00:19:42,290
This is my party.

477
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:45,590
Everypony is supposed to be
paying attention to me!

478
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:46,710
Whatever.

479
00:19:46,710 --> 00:19:50,170
We still think you're losers,
right, Diamond Tiara?

480
00:19:50,220 --> 00:19:52,130
Bump, bump,
sugar...rump?

481
00:19:52,180 --> 00:19:53,430
Not now, Silver Spoon.

482
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:58,720
Name's Scootaloo.

483
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:00,350
And I'm Sweetie Belle.

484
00:20:00,390 --> 00:20:03,020
Apple Bloom.

485
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:04,440
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

486
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:07,440
This song is so super!

487
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:09,530
[ Glasses clink ]

488
00:20:09,570 --> 00:20:12,400
[ Slurping ]

489
00:20:12,450 --> 00:20:14,740
So, I was thinking,
now that we're friends --

490
00:20:14,740 --> 00:20:17,450
I mean,
we are friends, right?

491
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:20,200
How could we not be?
We're totally alike.

492
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:21,540
We don't have
cutie marks,

493
00:20:21,580 --> 00:20:24,540
Diamond Tiara and Silver Spoon
drive us crazy.

494
00:20:24,580 --> 00:20:26,040
Totally crazy!

495
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:28,130
[ Laughter ]

496
00:20:28,130 --> 00:20:29,670
Well,
now that we're friends,

497
00:20:29,710 --> 00:20:32,010
what if the three of us
work together

498
00:20:32,050 --> 00:20:34,300
to find out who we are
and what we're supposed to be?

499
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,550
Ooh! Ooh!

500
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:38,140
We could form
our own secret society.

501
00:20:38,180 --> 00:20:40,520
I'm liking this idea.

502
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:43,100
A secret society.
Yeah.

503
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:44,640
We'll need a name for it,
though.

504
00:20:46,270 --> 00:20:48,610
The cutie-mark three?

505
00:20:48,650 --> 00:20:51,320
The cute-tastically
fantastics?

506
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:54,280
How about...
the cutie-mark crusaders?

507
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:55,280
It's perfect!

508
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:57,410
This is gonna be
so great!

509
00:20:57,450 --> 00:20:59,160
We're gonna be
unstoppable!

510
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,410
What do you say
we celebrate

511
00:21:00,450 --> 00:21:02,120
with some of these
delicious cupcakes?

512
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,210
Not the cupcakes!

513
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:05,500
Trust me.

514
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:07,670
Let's see if there are
any cookies.

515
00:21:07,710 --> 00:21:09,210
Yeah!
Come on.

516
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:11,380
Twilight Sparkle:
"Dearest Princess Celestia,

517
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:14,340
"I am happy to report that one
of your youngest subjects

518
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:17,760
"has learned a valuable lesson
about friendship.

519
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,430
"Sometimes the thing you think

520
00:21:19,470 --> 00:21:22,180
will cause you to lose friends
and feel left out..."

521
00:21:22,220 --> 00:21:23,520
"...can actually be the thing

522
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,560
"that helps you make
your closest friends

523
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:28,190
and realize how special
you are."

524
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:30,190
